1
00:00:00,484 --> 00:00:02,523
(One sunny spring day when you just can't stay in the classroom)

2
00:00:02,524 --> 00:00:03,524
What?

3
00:00:03,654 --> 00:00:05,453
You want the team to reach the round of 16, don't you?

4
00:00:05,454 --> 00:00:06,454
- I hope the team makes it...
- What are you guys doing?

5
00:00:06,455 --> 00:00:07,493
to the quarterfinals.

6
00:00:07,494 --> 00:00:09,663
- Hey, what's going on?
- Let's go out to the schoolyard.

7
00:00:09,664 --> 00:00:11,323
- That's random.
- We just got here.

8
00:00:11,324 --> 00:00:13,163
- Today...
- Don't you guys know?

9
00:00:13,164 --> 00:00:15,904
- What do you mean?
- The soccer festival...

10
00:00:16,104 --> 00:00:17,603
that sets the global mood...

11
00:00:17,604 --> 00:00:19,133
- and makes our hearts race, - That's right.

12
00:00:19,134 --> 00:00:23,744
the 2026 North and Central America Soccer Game is only 50 days away.

13
00:00:24,804 --> 00:00:26,444
Korea!

14
00:00:27,914 --> 00:00:29,513
This time,

15
00:00:29,514 --> 00:00:31,753
this Soccer Games will be co-hosted by three countries,

16
00:00:31,754 --> 00:00:34,453
which are the US, Mexico, and Canada,

17
00:00:34,454 --> 00:00:36,723
for the first time in the history of soccer games.

18
00:00:36,724 --> 00:00:38,523
- Aren't you excited?
- Of course, we are.

19
00:00:38,524 --> 00:00:40,393
On which channel can we watch the games?

20
00:00:40,394 --> 00:00:41,493
- Where should we watch them?
- Kyung Hoon.

21
00:00:41,494 --> 00:00:43,363
- Where do you think?
- Where should we watch them?

22
00:00:43,364 --> 00:00:45,133
You should watch the games with your wife.

23
00:00:45,134 --> 00:00:47,333
You should watch them on the channel your wife works for.

24
00:00:47,334 --> 00:00:48,903
Of course, you should watch them on JTBC.

25
00:00:48,904 --> 00:00:50,464
- JTBC!
- JTBC!

26
00:00:51,434 --> 00:00:53,103
- Oh, it fits the beat perfectly.
- Of course.

27
00:00:53,104 --> 00:00:55,043
For the most exciting and dynamic coverage,

28
00:00:55,044 --> 00:00:58,543
- watch the Soccer Games on JTBC!
- JTBC!

29
00:00:58,544 --> 00:01:01,413
- I'll be broadcasting the games.
- How?

30
00:01:01,414 --> 00:01:03,114
Well, I guess I'll have to discuss it with them.

31
00:01:04,214 --> 00:01:06,053
- You announced it before that?
- That's right.

32
00:01:06,054 --> 00:01:08,213
All the games are scheduled for the morning, Korean time.

33
00:01:08,214 --> 00:01:10,483
- That's perfect.
- They'll air at 10am or 11am.

34
00:01:10,484 --> 00:01:12,523
- I mean, the preliminary round.
- Players in Korean and abroad...

35
00:01:12,524 --> 00:01:14,353
- teams will play the games...
- Hey, we're here now.

36
00:01:14,354 --> 00:01:16,324
- You should all focus - Jong Seo is here.

37
00:01:17,564 --> 00:01:18,764
A legendary senior singer is here.

38
00:01:19,264 --> 00:01:20,293
- Kyun Sung!
- A legendary senior singer.

39
00:01:20,294 --> 00:01:21,664
What an unexpected combination!

40
00:01:22,064 --> 00:01:23,633
- Let us introduce ourselves.
- How are they here together?

41
00:01:23,634 --> 00:01:26,874
We're from We Kill It With Our High Notes High School.

42
00:01:27,204 --> 00:01:31,273
I'm Kim Jong Seo. I've been singing in the original key for 30 years.

43
00:01:31,274 --> 00:01:32,844
- Kim Jong Seo!
- That's amazing.

44
00:01:33,244 --> 00:01:36,513
I've been active as a member of Noel for 24 years...

45
00:01:36,514 --> 00:01:38,683
without a single member change. I'm Kang Kyun Sung.

46
00:01:38,684 --> 00:01:39,753
(Kang Kyun Sung has been a member of Noel for 24 years.)

47
00:01:39,754 --> 00:01:42,354
I'm the high-note diva. Just like Godiva,

48
00:01:42,454 --> 00:01:44,984
my high notes are like dark chocolate. I'm Lim Jeong Hee.

49
00:01:46,554 --> 00:01:49,963
I'm High Note To Be Continued, Wendy.

50
00:01:49,964 --> 00:01:51,224
- That's great. Wendy is here.
- Wendy!

51
00:01:51,594 --> 00:01:53,733
- This is the first show...
- Yes?

52
00:01:53,734 --> 00:01:56,133
I've been on since I was discharged from the military.

53
00:01:56,134 --> 00:01:57,563
- I'm deeply honored.
- Really?

54
00:01:57,564 --> 00:01:59,833
I'm the main vocalist of Wanna One...

55
00:01:59,834 --> 00:02:01,503
and the master of high notes. I'm Kim Jae Hwan.

56
00:02:01,504 --> 00:02:03,103
- Wanna One!
- Welcome!

57
00:02:03,104 --> 00:02:04,503
- You guys look amazing.
- What a diverse lineup of guests.

58
00:02:04,504 --> 00:02:05,513
- Looking at them, I realized...
- Jae Hwan, come to the back.

59
00:02:05,514 --> 00:02:07,473
that one of the guests has never come on the show before.

60
00:02:07,474 --> 00:02:09,783
- That's right.
- One of them came ten years ago.

61
00:02:09,784 --> 00:02:13,353
- Yes, one of them did.
- We have a diverse lineup today.

62
00:02:13,354 --> 00:02:14,413
- Don't you think so?
- You're right.

63
00:02:14,414 --> 00:02:16,554
Kyun Sung, you were incredible when you came here ten years ago.

64
00:02:17,084 --> 00:02:18,353
- Do you remember that?
- I remember that.

65
00:02:18,354 --> 00:02:20,323
- Well... Back then...
- He was unbelievable.

66
00:02:20,324 --> 00:02:21,763
Didn't you jump up and down...

67
00:02:21,764 --> 00:02:23,864
- holding a toy hammer?
- He hit us with that toy hammer...

68
00:02:24,024 --> 00:02:25,233
- with a strange look on his face.
- You know...

69
00:02:25,234 --> 00:02:27,194
- It's still a legendary episode.
- We...

70
00:02:28,194 --> 00:02:30,604
(Kyun Sung came on the show with his mid-length hair swaying.)

71
00:02:30,734 --> 00:02:32,134
(Hitting)

72
00:02:32,304 --> 00:02:34,134
(Laughing hysterically)

73
00:02:35,244 --> 00:02:37,404
(He swung the toy hammer around like he was playing Whac-A-Mole.)

74
00:02:37,974 --> 00:02:40,643
(He threw the whole class into chaos with his beautiful madness.)

75
00:02:40,644 --> 00:02:43,443
- I thought maybe I went too far.
- He looked scary.

76
00:02:43,444 --> 00:02:44,444
- No, you didn't.
- So I...

77
00:02:44,445 --> 00:02:45,583
That's not true, Kyun Sung.

78
00:02:45,584 --> 00:02:48,483
- I was worried a lot.
- How you acted in that episode...

79
00:02:48,484 --> 00:02:50,583
helped our show find its identity.

80
00:02:50,584 --> 00:02:52,193
- Is that right?
- Yes.

81
00:02:52,194 --> 00:02:54,523
Rather than the toy hammer, Kyun Sung's gaze scared me more.

82
00:02:54,524 --> 00:02:56,093
- His gaze was scary.
- Indeed.

83
00:02:56,094 --> 00:02:57,094
- He looked absolutely insane.
- Right.

84
00:02:57,095 --> 00:02:58,863
- He seemed so stressed out.
- Exactly.

85
00:02:58,864 --> 00:03:01,064
- I see we still have a toy hammer.
- What?

86
00:03:01,294 --> 00:03:03,064
- Why don't you hit Jong Seo?
- We have a toy hammer?

87
00:03:03,304 --> 00:03:05,103
- That's not... How could I...
- Right. Go ahead.

88
00:03:05,104 --> 00:03:06,873
- hit my senior singer?
- We're all friends here.

89
00:03:06,874 --> 00:03:09,304
I'm shrinking with age, so it's a bad idea.

90
00:03:09,704 --> 00:03:10,873
By the way, Sang Min, do you remember?

91
00:03:10,874 --> 00:03:12,443
- He and I have good memories...
- I think that's possible.

92
00:03:12,444 --> 00:03:13,973
from high school.

93
00:03:13,974 --> 00:03:15,283
- You and I?
- Yes.

94
00:03:15,284 --> 00:03:16,913
- From high school?
- I mean, when I was in high school.

95
00:03:16,914 --> 00:03:18,113
When you were in high school?

96
00:03:18,114 --> 00:03:19,954
- Next to 63 Building...
- Yes?

97
00:03:20,754 --> 00:03:21,953
- You don't remember that?
- Next to 63 Building?

98
00:03:21,954 --> 00:03:22,954
What...

99
00:03:22,955 --> 00:03:24,053
(Let's go back 10 years again.)

100
00:03:24,054 --> 00:03:26,754
(Kyun Sung asked Sang Min exactly the same question.)

101
00:03:26,954 --> 00:03:27,954
(I don't remember that.)

102
00:03:28,794 --> 00:03:30,863
- I never met you back then.
- What?

103
00:03:30,864 --> 00:03:32,293
- But...
- You don't remember that?

104
00:03:32,294 --> 00:03:34,594
(You don't remember that?)

105
00:03:34,864 --> 00:03:36,033
Why would you get mad at me?

106
00:03:36,034 --> 00:03:37,203
Why did you hit my desk?

107
00:03:37,204 --> 00:03:38,533
It's just because you're sitting in the front.

108
00:03:38,534 --> 00:03:39,673
But it's my desk.

109
00:03:39,674 --> 00:03:41,004
- Go and hit Sang Min's.
- It wasn't like that.

110
00:03:41,134 --> 00:03:42,603
(They reenacted the legendary scene after 10 years.)

111
00:03:42,604 --> 00:03:46,414
- Wendy and Jae Hwan...
- That was funny.

112
00:03:46,674 --> 00:03:47,743
haven't come on the show in a long while.

113
00:03:47,744 --> 00:03:49,243
- They came here...
- That's right.

114
00:03:49,244 --> 00:03:52,353
with their group members before.

115
00:03:52,354 --> 00:03:54,413
- They're not with them today.
- How do you feel...

116
00:03:54,414 --> 00:03:56,253
about being here alone without your group members?

117
00:03:56,254 --> 00:03:58,283
When I came here with my group members,

118
00:03:58,284 --> 00:04:00,023
- I could rely on them.
- Right.

119
00:04:00,024 --> 00:04:03,023
Today, I'm going to rely on my senior singers here.

120
00:04:03,024 --> 00:04:04,293
- Right.
- You can rely on us, Jae Hwan.

121
00:04:04,294 --> 00:04:06,163
- Hopefully, I'll have a lot of fun.
- That's good.

122
00:04:06,164 --> 00:04:08,764
I'm nervous as the other members are not here with me,

123
00:04:09,004 --> 00:04:10,104
but at the same time, I'm so excited.

124
00:04:10,164 --> 00:04:11,333
- Oh, I see.
- Yes.

125
00:04:11,334 --> 00:04:12,433
- What about you, Jae Hwan?
- When she was here ten years ago,

126
00:04:12,434 --> 00:04:14,734
- Wendy made me cry my eyes out.
- That's right.

127
00:04:15,304 --> 00:04:17,873
- I'll make you cry in another way.
- Oh, the counseling session?

128
00:04:17,874 --> 00:04:18,973
- While having a counseling...
- Oh, she asked for advice?

129
00:04:18,974 --> 00:04:20,413
While we were talking 1-on-1, you made me cry.

130
00:04:20,414 --> 00:04:21,414
- Right.
- Yes, I did.

131
00:04:22,344 --> 00:04:25,654
(10 years ago, during the counseling session,)

132
00:04:26,154 --> 00:04:28,484
(Wendy bombarded Ho Dong with compliments.)

133
00:04:28,784 --> 00:04:30,184
(I'm feeling shy. I feel like I'm going to cry.)

134
00:04:30,754 --> 00:04:32,724
(Picking up tissues)

135
00:04:33,394 --> 00:04:36,794
(I wanted to let you know that you were a good person.)

136
00:04:37,564 --> 00:04:40,194
(Wendy's unexpected comfort made Ho Dong cry tears.)

137
00:04:40,434 --> 00:04:42,563
I got compliments from many viewers after that.

138
00:04:42,564 --> 00:04:43,564
That's right.

139
00:04:44,264 --> 00:04:45,803
- It was too...
- By the way, it's obvious...

140
00:04:45,804 --> 00:04:47,433
- we're shooting a special episode.
- The energy...

141
00:04:47,434 --> 00:04:49,143
And I see that we're having "the high note special."

142
00:04:49,144 --> 00:04:50,303
- Right.
- All of our guests here...

143
00:04:50,304 --> 00:04:51,573
- are good at high notes.
- They're all masters of high notes.

144
00:04:51,574 --> 00:04:53,373
- Yes, they're all masters.
- That's right.

145
00:04:53,374 --> 00:04:55,984
You have a big age gap. Are you close with one another?

146
00:04:56,314 --> 00:04:58,484
- As for Jeong Hee, - Yes?

147
00:04:58,954 --> 00:05:00,654
both she and I used to work with JYP Entertainment.

148
00:05:01,214 --> 00:05:02,383
- We've known each other...
- You guys are close.

149
00:05:02,384 --> 00:05:04,154
since we were trainees.

150
00:05:04,454 --> 00:05:05,553
She was the best vocalist among us.

151
00:05:05,554 --> 00:05:07,153
That was how she seemed to us.

152
00:05:07,154 --> 00:05:08,893
- I'm flattered.
- And she's pretty too.

153
00:05:08,894 --> 00:05:10,593
- Oh, please.
- She also has a good personality.

154
00:05:10,594 --> 00:05:13,033
- Oh, my.
- So all the other trainees...

155
00:05:13,034 --> 00:05:14,693
- I mean, obviously, we all...
- Yes?

156
00:05:14,694 --> 00:05:15,803
- Did you all want to be like her?
- Did you...

157
00:05:15,804 --> 00:05:17,233
We all thought highly of her.

158
00:05:17,234 --> 00:05:18,333
(She was popular among the trainees.)

159
00:05:18,334 --> 00:05:20,374
- They all tried to be like her.
- You can stop here.

160
00:05:21,134 --> 00:05:23,074
Even though she's a good person and a great singer,

161
00:05:23,404 --> 00:05:24,903
we have a bit of a painful history.

162
00:05:24,904 --> 00:05:26,013
- What?
- Why?

163
00:05:26,014 --> 00:05:27,514
- Was it when you were a trainee?
- I can't...

164
00:05:28,644 --> 00:05:29,714
I can't tell the story by myself.

165
00:05:30,514 --> 00:05:31,913
- Jong Seo...
- Was he a trainee...

166
00:05:31,914 --> 00:05:33,883
(The story goes way back.)

167
00:05:33,884 --> 00:05:35,553
- Jong Seo...
- It must be a long time ago.

168
00:05:35,554 --> 00:05:37,623
If Jong Seo was a trainee...

169
00:05:37,624 --> 00:05:38,624
When was that?

170
00:05:38,625 --> 00:05:39,754
That must've been right after the Korean War.

171
00:05:40,254 --> 00:05:42,493
- Come on. That's nonsense.
- Since the Korean War...

172
00:05:42,494 --> 00:05:44,323
- The late period of Joseon Dynasty.
- Don't do that to Jong Seo.

173
00:05:44,324 --> 00:05:45,664
It was back in the early modernization period.

174
00:05:46,164 --> 00:05:47,833
- The early modernized period?
- In the Joseon Dynasty?

175
00:05:47,834 --> 00:05:48,933
It was around the time of the Gabo Reform of 1894.

176
00:05:48,934 --> 00:05:50,103
- The early modernized period.
- My gosh.

177
00:05:50,104 --> 00:05:51,363
Tell us your story.

178
00:05:51,364 --> 00:05:52,373
I can't tell the story.

179
00:05:52,374 --> 00:05:55,033
It's a painful memory for me, not for him.

180
00:05:55,034 --> 00:05:58,043
I competed on the show where the contestants wear a mask.

181
00:05:58,044 --> 00:06:00,613
I was on a six-time winning streak.

182
00:06:00,614 --> 00:06:02,013
Since I had won six times in a row,

183
00:06:02,014 --> 00:06:05,813
I felt relaxed, taking a nap in my green room before the shoot.

184
00:06:05,814 --> 00:06:07,353
The shoot began,

185
00:06:07,354 --> 00:06:08,453
and I found out it was Jong Seo.

186
00:06:08,454 --> 00:06:09,953
- Oh, I see where this is going.
- The one I'd compete against.

187
00:06:09,954 --> 00:06:13,293
I was full of hope of continuing my winning streak.

188
00:06:13,294 --> 00:06:14,923
But I ended up taking off my mask...

189
00:06:14,924 --> 00:06:16,064
- He ended your winning streak?
- Yes.

190
00:06:16,364 --> 00:06:19,193
Jong Seo ended my winning streak.

191
00:06:19,194 --> 00:06:20,194
I feel bad about it.

192
00:06:20,195 --> 00:06:21,393
Jong Seo, whom did you lose to?

193
00:06:21,394 --> 00:06:22,604
I don't remember that.

194
00:06:23,564 --> 00:06:25,403
- Of course.
- You don't remember that?

195
00:06:25,404 --> 00:06:27,273
- I refuse...
- It's not that you lost,

196
00:06:27,274 --> 00:06:29,773
- but you handed over the throne.
- I refuse to remember.

197
00:06:29,774 --> 00:06:32,643
You should go through the enrollment process now.

198
00:06:32,644 --> 00:06:34,043
- Didn't you prepare something?
- Yes, we did.

199
00:06:34,044 --> 00:06:35,684
- Yes, we prepared something.
- Good.

200
00:06:36,114 --> 00:06:37,844
(Trudging)

201
00:06:38,144 --> 00:06:39,983
- He looks like he'll do something.
- He scares me.

202
00:06:39,984 --> 00:06:41,213
- Kyun Sung looks scary.
- Do it where you are.

203
00:06:41,214 --> 00:06:42,653
- Look at his face. He's scary.
- You can just...

204
00:06:42,654 --> 00:06:46,394
- Don't take out anything weird.
- A dark cloud follows him.

205
00:06:46,924 --> 00:06:49,023
- This is the right document.
- Take it. It's our transfer form.

206
00:06:49,024 --> 00:06:52,663
It looks as if there were a dark cloud following Kyun Sung around.

207
00:06:52,664 --> 00:06:54,193
Why is Kyun Sung so scary?

208
00:06:54,194 --> 00:06:56,833
The transfer form to Men on a Mission.

209
00:06:56,834 --> 00:06:58,133
- Kim Jong Seo, Kang Kyun Sung, - Yes?

210
00:06:58,134 --> 00:06:59,973
Lim Jeong Hee, Wendy, and Kim Jae Hwan.

211
00:06:59,974 --> 00:07:02,773
(The masters of high notes, welcome.)

212
00:07:02,774 --> 00:07:05,543
Jeong Hee gave birth to a son last year.

213
00:07:05,544 --> 00:07:07,113
- Congratulations.
- Congratulations.

214
00:07:07,114 --> 00:07:08,814
(Lim Jeong Hee welcomed a son last September. Congratulations!)

215
00:07:09,384 --> 00:07:10,683
(Mom Jeong Hee brought news as warm as a spring breeze.)

216
00:07:10,684 --> 00:07:13,183
- Last year.
- Congratulations

217
00:07:13,184 --> 00:07:15,054
- Congratulations - She gave birth last year.

218
00:07:15,624 --> 00:07:16,624
(Huge congratulations on the birth of your son.)

219
00:07:16,625 --> 00:07:18,553
- She has a son now.
- Congratulations on your baby boy

220
00:07:18,554 --> 00:07:20,253
A surprise like this...

221
00:07:20,254 --> 00:07:22,563
might make me cry as my hormones haven't gone back to normal yet.

222
00:07:22,564 --> 00:07:25,433
So please don't surprise me like this.

223
00:07:25,434 --> 00:07:26,793
- You can go ahead and cry.
- It wasn't a surprise.

224
00:07:26,794 --> 00:07:28,493
Jeong Hee, if you cry,

225
00:07:28,494 --> 00:07:29,833
- it will be in the preview.
- We're sorry...

226
00:07:29,834 --> 00:07:31,603
we couldn't congratulate you last year.

227
00:07:31,604 --> 00:07:33,903
It's been exactly six months.

228
00:07:33,904 --> 00:07:36,804
- Six months?
- I gave birth last September.

229
00:07:37,074 --> 00:07:38,343
So it's been six months.

230
00:07:38,344 --> 00:07:41,673
I'm working on a new song album, fueled by the power of a mother.

231
00:07:41,674 --> 00:07:42,843
I'm preparing to make my comeback as a singer.

232
00:07:42,844 --> 00:07:45,043
- That's great. Congratulations.
- Congratulations.

233
00:07:45,044 --> 00:07:46,353
- Thank you.
- Stop applauding.

234
00:07:46,354 --> 00:07:47,613
She said it might make her cry.

235
00:07:47,614 --> 00:07:49,984
First, our guests...

236
00:07:50,084 --> 00:07:52,723
wrote their nicknames.

237
00:07:52,724 --> 00:07:53,823
I'm very curious.

238
00:07:53,824 --> 00:07:55,023
